value.title: President's job approval is surest sign Trump will lose reelection
value.excerpt: Just 37 percent of Americans approve of the president’s handling of the pandemic — and that is extremely problematic for him.

value.title: What Demi Lovato Says About Donald Trump in New Protest Song 'Commander in Chief'
value.excerpt: "Commander in Chief" is the former Disney star's protest anthem against the Republican candidate ahead of election day on November 3.

value.title: 'Suburban women, will you please like me?': Trump attempts to appeal to voter group he has struggled to reach
value.excerpt: "Suburban women, will you please like me? Please. Please. I saved your damn neighborhood, OK?" Trump said at a rally Tuesday.

value.title: Trump supporters in battleground states largely favor LGBTQ rights, poll finds
value.excerpt: Likely voters in 10 battleground states were found to overwhelmingly support LGBTQ rights, according to a survey by Hart Research and the Human Rights Campaign.

value.title: Trump to coronavirus victims: 'I feel your pain because I've felt your pain'
value.excerpt: The president told a crowd in Johnstown, Pennsylvania, that he "felt like Superman" after getting an experimental drug treatment for Covid-19 and that he's now "immune."

value.title: Trump's campaign nearly went broke for the 2020 home stretch amid Brad Parscale's $200 million budgeting misfire, Republicans tell Insider.
value.excerpt: Money has been tight for the 2020 reelection effort since the demotion of the Trump campaign manager, even as the president tweets that all is well.

value.title: Jim Acosta responds to pro-Trump crowd chanting 'CNN sucks'
value.excerpt: CNN's Chief White House Correspondent Jim Acosta responded to a pro-Trump crowd chanting "CNN sucks" at a rally for President Trump in Florida.

value.title: Trump attorneys ask Supreme Court for stay in Manhattan DA's tax case
value.excerpt: The president’s attorneys argue that the DA’s subpoena for his tax documents is 'overbroad' and lacks 'good faith.'

value.title: Mitt Romney criticizes Trump, Democrats as he decries 'vile' and 'hate-filled' state of American politics
value.excerpt: Utah Sen. Mitt Romney, the 2012 Republican nominee for president, directly criticized President Donald Trump and Speaker Nancy Pelosi.

value.title: Betting on the 'base' — can Trump win again?
value.excerpt: President Trump has said he intends to win the 2020 election the same way he won the 2016 election. Not with a popular vote strategy. With an electoral vote strategy. He expects his vaunted “base” — concentrated in a few crucial states — to deliver an electoral vote majority for him just as it did four years ago.

value.title: ‘Not Our Faith’: Bipartisan Christian Group Take On Trump In New Super PAC
value.excerpt: The new super PAC plans to roll out six-figure ads to erode Christian support for President Donald Trump in the last few weeks before the election.

value.title: Trump is lashing out at Fauci — and is ‘clearly in a place of desperation’: CNN political analyst
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Tuesday lashed out at Dr. Anthony Fauci after America’s top infectious disease expert objected to the Trump campaign taking his past statements out of context and using them in an election ad.

value.title: Back on campaign trail, Trump says he feels 'powerful' after COVID recovery
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump returned to the campaign trail on Monday for the first time since he announced his COVID-19 diagnosis, touting his management of the pandemic as opinion polls showed him losing more ground to Democratic rival Joe Biden.

value.title: Fauci: Trump ad taking him out of context 'really disappointing', should be taken down
value.excerpt: Asked by "The Lead" anchor Jake Tapper whether he believes the ad should be taken down, Fauci said, "I think so."

value.title: Columbus Day: Trump accuses 'radical activists' of trying to undermine explorer's legacy in holiday proclamation
value.excerpt: Trump used a typical White House holiday announcement to accuse "radical activists" of seeking to undercut Christopher Columbus' legacy.

value.title: 'Put these animals in jail': Trump condemns protestors in Portland and continues his 'law and order' campaign rhetoric
value.excerpt: Trump's comments are a continuation of attacks on Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden, who he has claimed is weak on "law and order."

value.title: Those waiting for Trump's 'middle-income tax cut' should give up
value.excerpt: Shortly before the 2018 elections, Trump made up a tax-cut idea that didn't exist in reality. Shortly before the 2020 elections, he's doing it again.

value.title: Ross Douthat column: There will be no Trump coup
value.excerpt: Three weeks from now, we will reach an end to speculation about what Donald Trump will do if he faces political defeat, whether he will leave power like a normal president or attempt some wild resistance.

value.title: What Trump could learn from the fall of France's own fiery 'law and order' president
value.excerpt: Americans are on the eve of a momentous political choice this November. But for a jump on how the story goes from here, consider what happened in France, where another "back to normal" candidate challenged a firebrand incumbent.

value.title: Cuban-Americans Hold Huge Pro-Trump Parade in South Florida as Elections Approach
value.excerpt: "Together with our Latin American brothers, we have a very clear message: Our moral priority is to defend the United States, the liberation of Cuba and the hemisphere with love," one organizer said.

value.title: Tupac's relative says the Trump campaign was 'clearly disrespectful' to leave a ticket for the late rapper at vice presidential debate
value.excerpt: The dig came after vice presidential nominee Kamala Harris said Tupac Shakur is the "best rapper alive" during a recent interview.

value.title: Pelosi calls latest Trump stimulus proposal 'grossly inadequate' as Trump revives push
value.excerpt: "It is hard to understand who is shaping their approach," Pelosi said of the Trump administration, "which to date has been a miserable and deadly failure."

value.title: Trump Has Called His Supporters ‘Disgusting.’ Do They Care?
value.excerpt: The people Trump despises most love him the most,” Howard Stern has said. But that may be beginning to change.

value.title: Election updates: Trump deemed 'safe' to return to public engagements, won't say if he's tested negative
value.excerpt: Trump's aides are working to satisfy his desire to get back out on the campaign trail as early as Monday in Pittsburgh.

value.title: In interview with Rush Limbaugh, Donald Trump calls LeBron James a 'hater' and 'nasty spokesman'
value.excerpt: During an interview on Rush Limbaugh's radio show Friday, Donald Trump brought up LeBron James, calling him a "hater" and a "nasty spokesman."

value.title: 'I shouldn't be here': Wisconsin bar owner in ICU with COVID-19 blames Trump for out-of-control pandemic
value.excerpt: The owner of a beloved Oshkosh bar is in the ICU with COVID-19 and blames the president for an out-of-control pandemic that has infected his family.

value.title: Candace Owens' BLEXIT group pays for some attendees' travel to Trump's White House event
value.excerpt: Some guests for Saturday's White House event featuring President Donald Trump had their travel and lodging paid for by Candace Owens' group, BLEXIT.

value.title: 'The president is likely toast': Trump's woes raise GOP fears of a blue wave
value.excerpt: "The president has had possibly the worst two-week stretch that a candidate could have going into the final month of an election," one Republican strategist said.

value.title: Schiff: If Trump wanted more infections 'would he be doing anything different'?
value.excerpt: Rep. Adam Schiff (D-Calif.) on Thursday tore into President Trump’s handling of the coronavirus, warning that a rally he plans to hold at the White House Saturday runs the risk of spreading the illness.

value.title: Trump Says Scans Found 'Congestion' In His Lungs, Doesn’t Know If He’s Virus-Free Yet
value.excerpt: Trump's physician Dr. Sean Conley, who has given conflicting reports on Trump's health, previously said that scans resulted in "expected findings."
